<h2>Solid State Relays</h2>

Solid State Relays (SSRs) are the heart of Parallel Port Control Boxes.
I find it easier to purchase pre-built SSRs, but you can build them 
(rather cheaply) if you know what your doing.  
<a href="http://drew.hickmans.net">Drew Hickman</a>
provides some good information on his 

<a href="http://drew.christmascave.com">Christmas site </a>
for 
<a href="http://drew.hickmans.net/switching_110VAC.htm">building SSRs</a>.

If you shop around, you can usually find <i>used</i> 110V 10A SSRs that will 
work with 5 vdc input for under $5 a piece (sometimes $3). 

<br><br>
All a Solid State Replay really does is allow the 110V AC current to pass
through when 3-8V DC is applied, and opens the AC circuit when the
direct current is not present.

