<h2>The Control Wires</h2>

The last piece of the puzzle is adding the control wires for the parallel port.
All I did is take a printer cable, and cut off the end that goes to the 
printer. Pins 2-9 on the parallel port cable should go to the individual
SSRs (HOT side)and the ground wire (usually back with white stripe) 
should connect to the NEUTRAL side of the SSRs.

